  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 230ºC/ 210ºC (fan)/ gas 8</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into batons</p><p>Add the <strong>carrot batons </strong>to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!) with a generous splash of <strong>cold water</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around them to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray (or two!), then put the tray[s] in the oven and cook for an initial 12 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707823544404-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707823544404-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707823544404-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707823544404-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707823544404-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel your <strong>potatoes </strong>and chop in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a large heat-proof bowl covered with<strong> cling film</strong></p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are slightly tender / fork tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707823551540-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707823551540-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707823551540-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707823551540-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707823551540-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the string from your <strong>beef joint[s]</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rub over your <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>coated beef</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707823556009-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707823556009-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707823556009-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707823556009-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707823556009-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has had an initial 12 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>(reserve the bowl for later!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>coated beef </strong>with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven and cook for 22-25 min or until the beef is cooked through and slightly pink inside</p><p>Tip: Prefer no pink meat? Cook your beef for 3-5 min longer!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707823560762-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707823560762-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707823560762-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707823560762-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707823560762-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wipe clean the reserved bowl and combine your <strong>crème fraîche </strong>and<strong> horseradish </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>horseradish crème fraîche</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707823566254-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707823566254-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707823566254-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707823566254-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707823566254-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has been cooking for 22-25 min, boil a kettle</p><p>Remove the <strong>beef</strong> from the oven, transfer it to a clean chopping board and leave to rest for 4-5 min – this is your <strong>mustard roast beef</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to the parcel with the carrot batons</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a final 4-5 min or until the potatoes are roasted and golden and the peas are warmed through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707823634252-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707823634252-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707823634252-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707823634252-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1707823634252-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once everything is nearly ready, combine your <strong>gravy base </strong>with 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> in a heatproof jug, whisk thoroughly</p><p>Put the jug in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 30-40 secs or until thickened and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707823639921-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707823639921-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707823639921-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707823639921-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707823639921-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested beef </strong>finely</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced beef </strong>with the <strong>roast potatoes</strong>,<strong> buttered veg </strong>and <strong>horseradish crème fraîche </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>gravy</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
